==English==
===Etymology===
From the English ''reflexion'', from the Late Latin ''reflexionem'', from ''reflexio''; the variant spelling ''reflection'' is due to influence from ''correction''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-reflection.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''reflexion'''
# the act of [[reflecting]], or the state of being [[reflected]]
# the [[property]] of a [[propogate]]d [[wave]] being thrown back from a [[surface]] (such as a [[mirror]])
# something, such as an [[image]], that is reflected
#:''The dog barked at his own '''reflexion''' in the mirror.''
# careful [[thought]] or [[consideration]]
#:''After careful '''reflexion''', I have decided not to vote for that proposition.''
# an [[implied]] [[criticism]]
#:''It is a '''reflexion''' on his character that he never wavered in his resolve.''

